  "name": "Lead Laser Cleaning Dataset",
  "description": "Cleaning lead with lasers is tricky due to its low melting point, leaving surfaces prone to heat damage in the process. I've gotten the best outcomes using lower power settings to gently strip away contaminants while keeping the material's dense structure intact for shielding applications, but always keep a close eye on it to avoid any softening or deformation at the end.",
